Bannerman Energy has announced that Steve Herlihy has been appointed as CFO and Company Secretary. Herlihy is a Chartered Accountant with over 30 years’ professional experience. His extensive background in the resources sector includes several roles within BHP, commencing as global Financial Controller for BHP Iron Ore before progressing to special project roles. More recently, he was a partner of a national accounting and advisory firm that was part of a top-ten global accounting network. Herlihy has deep, hands-on experience in project finance and M&A activities. His broad transactional experience ranges from negotiating small joint venture agreements through to lead commercial roles on large-scale multinational transactions. Herlihy replaces Rob Orr, who has served as CFO and Company Secretary for the past two years. Bannerman’s MD and CEO, Brandon Munro, says: “I am delighted to welcome Steve Herlihy to Bannerman as we progress through the final evaluation and advancement stages for our world-class Etango-8 Uranium Project in Namibia. Steve is an executive of proven calibre and extensive experience who adds further strategic, financing and transactional depth to the Bannerman team.”